This paper deals with the fundamental limits of wiretap channels, which are channels that allow for secure communication between two parties in the presence of an eavesdropper. The paper focuses on achieving maximal secret communication rate subject to reliability and secrecy constraints at a given blocklength. This topic falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves coding theory (cs.CC) and signal processing (cs.SI) techniques to derive the achievability and converse bounds. Finally, the paper also deals with Gaussian wiretap channels, which are commonly studied in multimedia (cs.MM) applications. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.CC, cs.SI, and cs.MM, in that order.
